**Duplicate function definition**

`buildNvidiaProvider` is declared twice back-to-back (and with identical bodies). This will cause a TypeScript compilation error (`Duplicate function implementation`) and block the build.

```suggestion

  return {
    baseUrl: NVIDIA_BASE_URL,
    api: "openai-completions",
    models: [
      {
        id: "nvidia/llama-3.1-nemotron-70b-instruct",

        reasoning: false,
        input: ["text"],
        cost: NVIDIA_DEFAULT_COST,
        contextWindow: NVIDIA_DEFAULT_CONTEXT_WINDOW,
        maxTokens: NVIDIA_DEFAULT_MAX_TOKENS,
      },
      {

body:
**Inconsistent model ID format**

Two NVIDIA model IDs use `nvidia.<name>` (dot) instead of the `nvidia/<name>` (slash) format used by the other NVIDIA entries. If the upstream OpenAI-compatible API expects the slash-form model IDs, these two entries will be unusable while the others work.

```suggestion
        id: "nvidia/nemotron-nano-12b-v2",
```

(And similarly for the 9B v2 model.)
